social_posts.post_text: Consider the glasses you’ve been wearing. The prejudgements, the lessons we were taught as children and as adults that shaped our thinking and how we see things, the insecurities we see when we look at ourselves in the mirror. What if you take those glasses off and put on a new set. This pair let’s you see your biggest insecurity as your strength.  It lets you open your mind to new concepts that may be contradictory to what you’ve learned as a child or even a few years ago, but concepts that make you stand taller and find yourself, your true identity… and these new glasses allow you to leave the judgements up to Jesus and give you vision to see other people like God sees them, like God created them.  Imagine the clarity you’d be given with those new set of glasses… no doubt they’ll get foggy once in a while or smudges on them, but that’s an easy fix… just keep your eyes fixed on Jesus, he’ll wipe them clean for you 😉😎🤓🙌☀️💝

I have stacks of journals that date back to my high school days. Probably filled most of them during my last year in college and first year in the “real world”. Lots of identity crises in those years. Escaping an abusive relationship, meeting my late husband Travis @travelingwithtrav, and starting a unpredictable, unstable career as an entrepreneur. Again, I find myself journaling a lot with this new chapter I find myself in. So much clarity as I throw words on a page without punctuation or worrying about finishing a complete sentence. I just write until my thoughts come to halt and that is usually many pages later and some kind of mind blowing conclusion or solution is written in ink ✍️ and then I go… ahhhhh that’s why I’m feeling the way I have been. 
✨One of my most recent epiphany’s-  being an introvert, I used to beg for alone time so I could recharge my battery. In that alone time, I wouldn’t use it wisely. I would go workout or go for a walk but I never would feel full, 100% recharged… I’d always get to maybe 80% at most. It didn’t matter how much alone time I was given, 2 hours, 2 days…  didn’t matter. I would still feel drained with a clogged brain.  Wonder why I could never give others energy, I barely had enough for myself. 
What changed?! 
I have more recently (starting in 2023) been spending that alone time (which is more often now with the loss of my other half) with the Lord. I’ve been praying for a deeper relationship with Jesus. The Holy Spirit has been with me since I was born again 11 years ago, but now I’m seeking His guidance everyday, feeling His love and faithfulness every single day, witnessing His blessings all around me. It makes me thirsty for more. I can’t get enough of His Word. It speaks to me… and I find myself not just 100% but overflowing!!! Because of Him I feel more alive and have so much more to give to others!! Just had to share. ❤️🙏 Have a blessed Sunday 
.
.
.
#Godisgood #filledwiththeholyspirit

Tomorrow marks the beginning of a new chapter for me and I couldn’t be more excited about it!! I’ve spent countless hours with the Lord this year so far as we dig a little deeper together in finding who I am and what I’m meant to do with the time He is giving me. Of course He likes to hold his cards close and not reveal too much at a time but that is okay!! He knows me well and if He throws too much at me, I’ll get paralysis by over-analysis! Thank you to so so many of you that have always supported and prayed for me, my family, and my businesses over the years!! I hope to be just as supportive to you as well!! 

“For we walk by faith, not by sight.” 2 Corinthians 5:7

✨WHEN you have a gut feeling about something, you just gotta run with it!! 

✨WHEN some people think it’s silly, and others tell you it’s brilliant, you know you’re in the right place… 

✨WHEN everything aligns from all your past experiences and education, you have all the resources you need, plus a clear vision of what you want to accomplish, you go all in! 

✨WHEN you find a partner that is as equally driven as you and shares the same vision, you make it happen! 

✨WHEN you see 11 year olds out on the court playing across from 70 olds, it makes you stop and smile. 

✨WHEN you realize Life is too short to do anything that doesn’t bring joy and happiness to you and others, and ultimately glory to God, you make big decisions out of faith and the Holy Spirit helps to see it through! 

If you haven’t figured it out yet… @nickholley07 and I have started the @travelpickleballclub !! We want to bring our love of pickleball to all by offering affordable trips that bring like-minded, adventurous, and fun-loving people of all ages and skill levels to participate and form strong bonds as they try new things and are pushed beyond their comfort zones! 

Our first trip to Gatlinburg one week ago was a success in accomplishing just that and we look forward to growing our community and bringing people together in such a way that leaves a lasting impression and lasting memories!!

@travelpickleballclub officially launched with our first trip being in Gatlinburg/Sevierville, Tennessee just in time for beautiful fall weather at the beginning of October🍁! It was such an awesome group of people!! We stayed in a cabin with some incredible views, saw a black bear, split the group up into red and blue teams and did some team challenges, played pickleball in the rain and sun, day and night, hiked rainbow falls and Quillium Cave, went go-karting and had fire and hot tub time at night after dinner was cooked and we were all showered up!! 

Thank you to our partners @be.underestimated @wes.farm.soap @iconmeals @ghostpickleball @goldenpickleball

The addiction is real 😅 

Pickleball has been a much needed activity in my life this year and I’m loving the community at all the courts I find!

Here we are, well into the last month of 2023. How fast does time fly?! Much to reflect on, much has been discovered, as well as been revealed, much more to explore, learn, build, and pray about. I’m so thankful for family, for the unconditional friendships, and for Jesus.  Can’t wait to celebrate His birthday in a couple weeks 😁  Happy Holidays 🎄

I’ve had several doors close in 2023. I lost my husband of 14 years and father to our 12 year old twins @travelingwithtrav, partnerships in two different businesses ended, and along with that some friendships too, but I’m so grateful for the doors that have opened this past year as well. God is so good. I continue to lean on Him through all my trials. I’m constantly reminded how weak I am without Him. But he also shows me how strong I can be WITH HIM.  I still have a lot of healing to do… (kids too) but I’m very hopeful for all the blessings this year will bring. ❤️🙏😌
.
.
#healing #journey #hope #Godisgood
